## 🔧 GDScript Class Requirements

### Essential Classes
```
Card.gd - Card data + methods
CardDatabase.gd - Load/manage 200 cards
CardEnhanceSystem.gd - Enhancement logic (100% success)
Equipment.gd - Equipment data + methods
EquipmentDatabase.gd - Load/manage 66 equipment
EquipmentEnhanceUI.gd - Enhancement UI
LevelSystem.gd - XP/level with auto stats
MilestoneRewardSystem.gd - Milestone triggers + rewards
ContentUnlockManager.gd - Content unlock by level
GachaSystem.gd - Gacha pull logic
DropRateTable.gd - Rarity drop rates
GachaUI.gd - Gacha UI + animations
EconomyManager.gd - Gold/Diamond management
```

---

## 💡 Key Design Principles

### Automatic Progression
- Player has NO stat point choices
- All growth is automatic on level up
- Goal: Simple, low-maintenance gameplay

### 100% Success Rates
- No failure mechanics on enhancement
- All upgrades are guaranteed
- Clear cost → clear reward relationship

### Infinite Growth
- No level cap (endless progression)
- Consistent monetization (more gacha to progress faster)
- Endless content (new milestones at Lv 75, 100, 150, 200, 500, 1000)

### Dual Gacha System
- Equipment & Cards are separate pools
- Both have same base cost (50D)
- Both follow same rarity distribution
- Allows independent balancing

---

## ⚠️ Common Pitfalls (Avoid!)

```
❌ Adding Trait Mastery back (EXCLUDED on purpose)
❌ Manual stat point distribution (Use auto-only)
❌ Enhancement failure mechanics (100% success only)
❌ Cross-enhancement (equipment↔cards is FORBIDDEN)
❌ Hidden complexity (All formulas must be transparent)
```

